
This image illustrates the DevOps lifecycle, which combines software development (Dev) and IT operations (Ops) into a continuous process. 
Continuous Development: Bridges the gap between development and operations teams through automation and collaboration. 
Workflow Phases: Includes key steps like planning, coding, building, testing, releasing, deploying, and monitoring. 
Goal: Aims to streamline software delivery, foster collaboration, and expedite the release of high-quality softwar
